1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Kitten Economics Episode 4: Marginal Utility.

2
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Welcome back. Today we learn one core economics idea with kittens.

3
00:00:45,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Luna the kitten loves tuna bites.

4
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:45,000
The first bite feels amazing, the second is still great, and the sixth feels ordinary. This is marginal utility: each extra unit gives less additional satisfaction.

5
00:01:45,000 --> 00:02:10,000
The idea helps with spending. The first purchase may create real value, but repeated impulse purchases often add less joy.

6
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Recap: Marginal Utility. Use this rule in real decisions. Comment: More Kitten Economics.
